<div class="ref-intro">
  <h1>Webhooks</h1>
  <p>Register HTTP endpoints to receive real-time notifications when boards, cards, columns, or attachments change. Webhooks fire from <strong>all interfaces</strong> — web UI, CLI, REST API, MCP server, and SDK — ensuring consistent delivery regardless of how a mutation is triggered.</p>
  <ul class="capability-list">
    <li>20+ event types covering boards, cards, columns, comments, attachments, and forms</li>
    <li>HMAC-SHA256 signature verification with optional per-webhook secrets</li>
    <li>Manage via CLI (<code>kl webhooks add</code>), REST API, SDK, or MCP tools</li>
    <li>Powered by the <code>kl-webhooks-plugin</code> package with built-in fallback</li>
    <li>Registrations stored in <code>.kanban.json</code> and persist across restarts</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="usage-example">
    <strong>Register a webhook</strong>
    <pre><code>kl webhooks add \
  --url https://example.com/hook \
  --events task.created,task.moved \
  --secret mykey</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>

